First, we identify the relevant items and then compute the ratios step by step.

Step 1. Quick Ratio
• Quick assets include: Cash on Hand, Bank Deposits, Interest Receivable, Accounts Receivable.
  = 1,753,673.43 + 1,522,888.62 + 5,758.38 + 1,988,616.02
  = 5,270,936.45
• Current liabilities include: Accounts Payable + Taxes Payable.
  = 2,100,000.00 + 391,297.55
  = 2,491,297.55
• Quick Ratio = Quick Assets / Current Liabilities
  = 5,270,936.45 / 2,491,297.55 ≈ 2.12

Step 2. Net Profit Margin
• Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%
• From the income statement, Net Profit = –1,401,436.89 and Total Revenue = 7,825,951.24.
  = (–1,401,436.89 / 7,825,951.24) × 100% ≈ –17.90%

Thus, the answer is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Quick Ratio": "2.12",
    "Net Profit Margin": "-17.90%"
  }
}
